H0.text: Element symbols are most likely placed along the y-axis, the vertical axis of a graph.

H1.text: Negative numbers are most likely placed along the y-axis, which is the vertical axis on a graph.

H2.text: Dependent variables are most likely placed along the y-axis, which is the vertical axis on a graph.

H3.text: Independent variables are most likely placed along the y-axis of a graph.

A4.text: In statistics, more specifically in linear regression, a scatter plot of data is generated with X as the independent variable and Y as the dependent variable.

A5.text: The most common symbol for the input is x, and the most common symbol for the output is y; the function itself is commonly written y = f(x).
